Has 
...................
................
Use has with:

He She It Raju Rani Everybody Someone Anyone
Any singular noun (customer, employee, student, manager, etc.)

He has a laptop.             he doesn't have a laptop
Raju has a laptop.           Raju doesn't have a laptop.
employee has an id card      employee does't have a id card

Do
.................
Rule
Use do with:

I You We They
Plural nouns (children, workers, students, employees, etc.)

I do my homework every day.          I don't go to the office on Sunday. 
You do your work sincerely.          You don't speak French. 
We do our duty.                       We don't play cricket every day       
They do their jobs well.              They don't eat fast food.
Children do their homework.          Children don't watch TV during class.
Workers do their work carefully.     Workers don't arrive late.

